---
// SerpRouting — Chapter 084 Lesson 6, "hreflang, per-locale canonicals, and SEO".
//
// The lesson's primary visual: the user-facing stake of the whole topic. Same
// French query, two outcomes, side by side so the eye catches the single
// difference — which page Google serves and how the user reacts.
//
//   ┌── Without hreflang ──┐   ┌── With hreflang ──┐
//   │  [query: fr]         │   │  [query: fr]      │   (identical top)
//   │        ↓             │   │        ↓          │
//   │  English /billing    │   │  French /fr-FR/…  │   (diverges here)
//   │        ↓             │   │        ↓          │
//   │  ✗ Bounces (red)     │   │  ✓ Engaged (green)│
//   └──────────────────────┘   └───────────────────┘
//
// Built as a custom two-panel HTML/CSS layout (not TabbedContent) because the
// pedagogy is direct comparison — both columns must be visible at once so the
// reader literally sees the same query produce two served URLs. Flat boxes,
// thin borders, CSS-only downward arrows, a cross/check glyph on the outcome
// chip. The two panels are visually parallel; only the served URL and the
// outcome color differ, which is exactly the point.
//
// Mid-tone red/green (600-range) carry the signal in both themes; the rest of
// the chrome is theme-aware via Starlight gray/bg vars. `not-content` +
// margin:0 resets defeat Starlight's injected prose margins inside the figure.

import Figure from '../../../figures/Figure.astro';
---

<Figure expandable={false}>
	<div class="serp not-content">
		{/* LEFT — without hreflang: Google falls back to raw authority, serves English. */}
		<section class="serp-panel" aria-label="Without hreflang">
			<header class="serp-head serp-head-bad">Without hreflang</header>

			<div class="serp-bar">
				<span class="serp-search-icon" aria-hidden="true">🔍</span>
				<span class="serp-query">logiciel de facturation</span>
				<span class="serp-locale-pill">fr</span>
			</div>

			<div class="serp-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

			<div class="serp-result">
				<div class="serp-result-url">app.example.com/billing</div>
				<div class="serp-result-title">Billing software — Acme</div>
				<div class="serp-result-snippet">
					Send invoices, track payments, and manage subscriptions for your
					team…
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="serp-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

			<div class="serp-outcome serp-outcome-bad">
				<span class="serp-outcome-glyph" aria-hidden="true">✗</span>
				<span>Lands on English. Bounces.</span>
			</div>
		</section>

		{/* RIGHT — with hreflang: the cluster routes the French variant to her. */}
		<section class="serp-panel" aria-label="With hreflang">
			<header class="serp-head serp-head-good">With hreflang</header>

			<div class="serp-bar">
				<span class="serp-search-icon" aria-hidden="true">🔍</span>
				<span class="serp-query">logiciel de facturation</span>
				<span class="serp-locale-pill">fr</span>
			</div>

			<div class="serp-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

			<div class="serp-result">
				<div class="serp-result-url">app.example.com/fr-FR/billing</div>
				<div class="serp-result-title">Logiciel de facturation — Acme</div>
				<div class="serp-result-snippet">
					Envoyez des factures, suivez les paiements et gérez les abonnements de
					votre équipe…
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="serp-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></div>

			<div class="serp-outcome serp-outcome-good">
				<span class="serp-outcome-glyph" aria-hidden="true">✓</span>
				<span>Lands on French. Engaged.</span>
			</div>
		</section>
	</div>

	<Fragment slot="caption">
		The identical French query <em>logiciel de facturation</em> produces two
		different results. <strong style="color:#dc2626;">Without hreflang</strong>,
		Google can't tell the variants apart and serves the higher-authority
		English page — she bounces.
		<strong style="color:#16a34a;">With hreflang</strong>, the variants form a
		cluster and Google routes her to the French URL. One set of tags is the
		difference between capturing that organic traffic and handing it to a
		competitor.
	</Fragment>
</Figure>

<style>
	.serp {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 20px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 8px 4px;
		font-family:
			ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
	}

	/* Each column is one self-contained "what Google does" story. */
	.serp-panel {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: stretch;
		gap: 0;
		flex: 1 1 200px;
		min-width: 0;
		max-width: 340px;
		padding: 14px 16px 16px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Panel header — the only place the two columns are labeled differently. */
	.serp-head {
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.06em;
		text-align: center;
		padding: 5px 0;
		border-radius: 7px;
		margin: 0 0 14px;
	}
	.serp-head-bad {
		color: #b91c1c;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #dc2626 12%, transparent);
	}
	.serp-head-good {
		color: #15803d;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #16a34a 12%, transparent);
	}

	/* Stylized Google search bar — identical in both panels. */
	.serp-bar {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 6px;
		padding: 7px 10px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-7, #f8fafc);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-search-icon {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		font-size: 0.72rem;
		line-height: 1;
		opacity: 0.7;
	}
	.serp-query {
		flex: 1 1 auto;
		min-width: 0;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		font-style: italic;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
		overflow: hidden;
		text-overflow: ellipsis;
		white-space: nowrap;
		margin: 0;
	}
	/* The "fr" pill marks the searcher's language — same on both sides. */
	.serp-locale-pill {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		font-size: 0.6rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		color: #1d4ed8;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #2563eb 14%, transparent);
		border-radius: 5px;
		padding: 2px 6px;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* CSS-only downward connector between stages. */
	.serp-arrow {
		align-self: center;
		width: 2px;
		height: 22px;
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
		position: relative;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-arrow::after {
		content: '';
		position: absolute;
		left: 50%;
		bottom: -1px;
		transform: translateX(-50%);
		border-left: 5px solid transparent;
		border-right: 5px solid transparent;
		border-top: 6px solid var(--sl-color-gray-4, #94a3b8);
	}

	/* Stylized search result — the diverging payload. */
	.serp-result {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3px;
		padding: 10px 12px;
		border-radius: 9px;
		border: 1px solid var(--sl-color-gray-5, #cbd5e1);
		background: var(--sl-color-gray-7, #f8fafc);
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-result-url {
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		line-height: 1.2;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		word-break: break-all;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-result-title {
		font-size: 0.92rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: #1a56db;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-result-snippet {
		font-size: 0.74rem;
		line-height: 1.4;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* Outcome chip — red cross vs green check, the visual verdict. */
	.serp-outcome {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		padding: 8px 12px;
		border-radius: 9px;
		font-size: 0.82rem;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.25;
		margin: 0;
	}
	.serp-outcome-glyph {
		flex: 0 0 auto;
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 20px;
		height: 20px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
	}
	.serp-outcome-bad {
		color: #b91c1c;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #dc2626 10%, transparent);
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, #dc2626 35%, transparent);
	}
	.serp-outcome-bad .serp-outcome-glyph {
		background: #dc2626;
	}
	.serp-outcome-good {
		color: #15803d;
		background: color-mix(in srgb, #16a34a 10%, transparent);
		border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, #16a34a 35%, transparent);
	}
	.serp-outcome-good .serp-outcome-glyph {
		background: #16a34a;
	}

	/* Narrow viewports: the two panels stack; flex-wrap already handles it. */
	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.serp-panel {
			max-width: 100%;
		}
	}
</style>
